Name: UCSB
Description: The University of California, Santa Barbara (a public research school) is #5 in Top Public Schools in the nation according to U.S. News & World Report. It is one of the 10 campuses of the University of California system.

Name: Greyhound Rock
Description: On the coast of Northern California, Greyhound Rock is only accessible to people during low tides. It is home to a very diverse aquatic ecosystem.

Name: Twin Peaks
Description: Two hills in the "City by the Bay" where people gather to see the incredible views of San Francisco.

Name: Stanislaus National Forest
Description: A national forest in Northern California next to Yosemite National Park.

Name: Sands Beach
Description: A beach in Isla Vista where many UCSB students and local residents go to surf, watch the sunset, and enjoy time with friends!

Name: Ferry Building
Description: On the Embarcadero, the Ferry Building is a marketplace and gathering of " local farmers, artisan producers, and independently owned and operated food businesses".
